Package: sgs
Title: Sparse-group SLOPE: adaptive bi-level selection with FDR control
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(
	person("Fabio", "Feser", , "ff120@ic.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID")
      ),
        person("Marina", "Evangelou", role = "aut")
     )
Description: Implementation of Sparse-group SLOPE: Adaptive bi-level with FDR-control and applications in genetics (Bogdan et al. (2015) <doi:10/gfgwzt>). Linear and logistic regression models are supported, both of which can be fit using k-fold cross-validation. Dense and sparse input matrices are supported. In addition, a general adaptive three operator splitting (ATOS) implementation is provided.
